snippet.textDisplay: I really hope AMD is observing and learning lessons from Intel's struggles with these hardware exploits. That they're spending their Zen-early-years well, weeding out potential exploits, and hardening architectural and function security - *before* they are "publicly" known or become 0-day exploits. There's no replacement for fixing these kinds of things in-silicon. AMDs time _will_ come for more exploits, as more hardware(-based) security features arrive, and their blooming market and industry share make their CPUs and platforms a growing target for this stuff.
snippet.textOriginal: I really hope AMD is observing and learning lessons from Intel's struggles with these hardware exploits.
